	"metadata": {
		"title": "kernel: USB-accessible buffer overflow in brcmfmac (moderate)",
		"reference": [
			{
				"ref_id": "CVE-2022-3628",
				"ref_url": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2022-3628",
				"source": "CVE"
			}
		],
		"description": "DOCUMENTATION: A buffer overflow flaw was found in the Linux kernel Broadcom Full MAC Wi-Fi driver. This issue occurs when a user connects to a malicious USB device. This can allow a local user to crash the system or escalate their privileges. \n            \n            MITIGATION: To mitigate this issue, prevent the brcmfmac module from being loaded. See https://access.redhat.com/solutions/41278 for how to blacklist a kernel module to prevent it from loading automatically.",
